# ── Parley — secrets template ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env` and paste the values Band showed you (the API Key is
# shown ONCE when you click "Connect Remote Agent" — if you missed it, regenerate
# it on the agent's page). `.env` is gitignored and will NOT be committed.
#
# TWO-OPERATOR SETUP (the real cross-org trust boundary — see JOIN.md):
#   Operator A (Northwind / buyer) fills ONLY the Org-A section, then:
#       uv run python scripts/run_org.py buyer
#   Operator B (Lumen / owner) fills ONLY the Org-B section, then:
#       uv run python scripts/run_org.py owner
#   Each runs on their own machine with their own Band account + Claude/vendor auth.
#   (Solo demo: one person fills both sections and runs both sides.)

# === Band agents — Org A: Northwind Analytics (Operator A — buyer) ===
#   Register at app.band.ai -> Agents -> New Agent -> External Agent (handle northwind-analytics).
COORDINATOR_AGENT_ID=
COORDINATOR_API_KEY=

MODELER_AGENT_ID=
MODELER_API_KEY=

CHECKER_AGENT_ID=
CHECKER_API_KEY=

# === Band agent — Org B: Lumen Retail (Operator B — owner / the recruited stranger) ===
# A SEPARATE Band account from Org A (that's the whole point — a real second org).
# Operator B registers @lumen-retail/vault and fills only these two values.
VAULT_AGENT_ID=
VAULT_API_KEY=

# === Models ===
# All agents think via your Claude SUBSCRIPTION through the Claude Agent SDK /
# Claude Code (NO API key needed). Make sure Claude Code is installed & logged in.
# (Only fill this if we later decide to use a paid Anthropic API key instead.)
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# === Cross-VENDOR stranger (optional) ===
# Run the recruited custodian (@lumen-retail/vault) on a GENUINELY DIFFERENT,
# non-Claude vendor than the requester — a real cross-org AND cross-vendor
# handshake. Any OpenAI-compatible provider works through one path. First:
#   pip install -e ".[cross-vendor]"     (or: uv sync --extra cross-vendor)
# Then pick a vendor + key (Groq & OpenRouter have instant free keys):
#
#   Groq (free, fast Llama):   https://console.groq.com/keys
# VAULT_LLM_VENDOR=groq
# GROQ_API_KEY=
#
#   OpenRouter (one key, many models):  https://openrouter.ai/keys
# VAULT_LLM_VENDOR=openrouter
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
#
#   Any OpenAI-compatible endpoint (self-host / proxy / OpenAI):
# VAULT_LLM_VENDOR=custom
# VAULT_LLM_BASE_URL=https://your-endpoint/v1
# VAULT_LLM_API_KEY=                  # universal key (works for any vendor above too)
# VAULT_LLM_MODEL=                    # optional model override (e.g. openai/gpt-oss-120b)

# === Band platform endpoints (defaults — usually leave commented) ===
# BAND_REST_URL=https://app.band.ai
# BAND_WS_URL=wss://app.band.ai/api/v1/socket/websocket
